# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# crontab.example  -  Linux / macOS cron schedule for the AI-labor refresh.
#
# Install with:   crontab -e     (then paste the line below, edited for paths)
# List current:   crontab -l
#
# Cadence rationale:
#   * BLS OEWS updates ONCE a year (spring). O*NET updates QUARTERLY.
#   * So a WEEKLY check is more than enough. The pipeline exits immediately
#     ("NO_UPDATES") when nothing changed, so frequent runs are cheap.
#
# The 5 fields are:  minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Every Monday at 06:15, check for new data and (with --load in the script)
# refresh Snowflake. Set AI_LABOR_HOME so the wrapper finds the project.
15 6 * * 1  AI_LABOR_HOME=/Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake /Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake/scheduling/run_refresh.sh

# --- Alternatives ----------------------------------------------------------
# Daily at 06:15 (cheap because it no-ops when nothing changed):
# 15 6 * * *  AI_LABOR_HOME=/Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake /Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake/scheduling/run_refresh.sh
#
# First day of each quarter at 07:00 (aligns with O*NET's quarterly cadence):
# 0 7 1 1,4,7,10 *  AI_LABOR_HOME=/Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake /Users/you/ai_labor_snowflake/scheduling/run_refresh.sh
